User Stories and Acceptance Criterion Frame

User Story 1: Player Starts the Game
As a player,
I want to start a new game by pressing a “Start” button,
So that I can begin playing Power-Up Tetris Mayhem and enjoy the game.
Acceptance Criteria:
	•	The player must be able to click a visible “Start Game” button.
	•	Upon clicking, the game must transition from the main menu to the gameplay screen without delay.
	•	The game screen must display a timer or score tracker as soon as the game begins.

User Story 2: Player panda punch
As a player,
I want to be able to punch a panda 
So that I can collect bamboo 
Acceptance Criteria:
	•	when player left clicks panda, panda takes damage 
    •   when panda takes damage, bamboo is added to the bamboo count.

User Story 3: Upgrades
As a player,
I want to be able to buy upgrades
So that I can punch pandas for more bamboo
Acceptance Criteria:
	•   Have clickable buttons for each upgrade option
    •   Increase punching power or other upgrades to gain more bamboo

